    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9600 AND 9700 SLEEPER AND NON-SLEEPER CABS -
        SHEET METAL REPAIRS - ALIGN AND CLAMP NEW PANEL TO BODY OPENING
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="align" graphiccount="1">
        <title>ALIGN AND CLAMP NEW PANEL TO BODY OPENING</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply body sealer around outside perimeter of opening.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check positioning of air inlet vent seal, wiring, spacers, speed nuts, etc., which are
                located behind panel.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert turn signal wire through panel hole and align panel to opening (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600669">Figure 69</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1600669" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1600669" filename="../figg16/G1600669.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 69. Aligning New Panel To Cab</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Temporarily clamp panel in place, using C-clamps and install bolts in existing grille
                bracket mounting holes.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
